

Paul has made a tool to create the runlet lists from the DB for a given 
slug.  The slug numbers have to be put into the database first.

get_runlet_lists.pl

usage:  make_runlists.pl [-h] [-n <server] [-u <user>] [-d <database>]
                         [-t <target>] [-s <slug #>]

  -h : Print this help message.

  -n <server>   : Select database server (default:  cdaql6.jlab.org)
  -u <server>   : Select database user   (default:  qweak)
  -d <database> : Select database        (default:  qw_fall2010_20101204)

  -t <target>   : Name of target position (default: HYDROGEN-CELL)
                  Use 'all' to print run lists for all target positions
                  Use 'list' to list the available target names
                  Use 'notest' to disable sorting based on slow controls
  -s <slug #>   : Desired slug number (default:  0)
                  Use 'list' to print available slug numbers
